From: hr@company.com
To: all-employees@company.com
Subject: Important: Updated Remote Work Policy - Effective Feb 1, 2024
Date: Fri, 19 Jan 2024 11:00:00 +0530

Dear Team,

We're excited to announce our updated Remote Work Policy, effective February 1, 2024. This policy reflects our commitment to work-life balance while maintaining productivity and collaboration.

New Policy Highlights:

Hybrid Work Model:
- Employees can work remotely up to 3 days per week
- Mandatory in-office days: Tuesday and Thursday
- Flexible choice for Monday, Wednesday, Friday
- Core hours: 10 AM - 4 PM (must be available)

Remote Work Eligibility:
- All full-time employees after 3 months of employment
- Part-time employees: case-by-case basis
- Interns: must work from office (training purposes)

Equipment & Support:
- Company-provided laptop and accessories
- Monthly internet allowance: ₹1,500
- Ergonomic chair reimbursement: up to ₹15,000
- IT support available 24/7

Expectations:
- Maintain regular communication via Slack/Teams
- Attend all scheduled meetings (video on)
- Complete daily check-ins with your manager
- Respond to messages within 2 hours during core hours
- Meet all deadlines and deliverables

Office Amenities:
- Free lunch on in-office days
- Parking reimbursement
- Gym membership discount
- Childcare facilities available

Application Process:
1. Discuss with your manager
2. Fill out the Remote Work Agreement form
3. Submit to HR by January 26
4. Approval within 3 business days

Important Notes:
- Policy subject to review every 6 months
- Managers may require in-office presence for specific projects
- Abuse of policy may result in revocation of remote work privileges

We believe this policy will enhance employee satisfaction while maintaining our collaborative culture. Please reach out to hr@company.com with any questions.

Thank you,
Human Resources Team
